Agar ham Dhyaan se isse mehsoos kre toh maa sati aur mahadev ki katha lagta hai ye music...
Ekant wasi Shiv jo sansari nahi hai bairagi hai unka ehsaas... Maa sati ki chavi ka ehsaas... Unke shudh prem aur vivah ka drushy aur maa sati ka apne pita k yha yagy me jane ka hat...aur waha jana phir waha apne swami ka apmaan dekh kr aatmglani me agni ka awahan kar khud ko agni me samarpit karna... mahadev ko iska pata chalna aur sati maa k virah me krodh aur asahay ho kar sansaar me nisahay ho kar gumha maa sati k viyog me.... mere aakho k samne ye pura scene chal rha tha music k saath...

Indian music has classical but I feel with that, there has to be a Indian mythology/cultural based, ritual, medieval, mythical, dark, atmospheric genres combined music like how Scandinavia has Norse & Viking music or Ireland has Celtic music. 
Navarasam - Thaikdudam Bridge
Shiva Tandava Stotram - Uma Mohan
Paiyada - Ram Sampath & Aruna Sairam (Coke Studio)
May be Rakht Charitra title track too. 

Append to this list if I have missed anything obvious. It's also okay to add YouTubers who create & produce such music too.
